 diminutive of Gaelic <i>damh</i> ‘bard, poet’.","French: diminutive of   Cave  ."]},{"name":"Caves","meanings":["English: variant of   Cave  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Keeve","meanings":["English: perhaps a variant of   Cave  . This surname is rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Chaffee","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): descriptive nickname from a derivative of Old French <i>chauf</i> ‘bald’ (from Latin <i>calvus</i>). Compare   Cave  ."]},{"name":"Cavett","meanings":["Scottish (of French origin): altered form of French <b>Cavet</b>, which is either a diminutive of   Cave   3 or a metonymic occupational name for a laborer, one who used a <i>cavet</i>, an Old Occitan word for a tool for clearing ground for cultivation."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret de Cave was born in 1059, in Normandy, France as the daughter of Robert FitzBrian de Cave and Unknown. She married Gerald de Furnival I. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1112, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1059–1112":"1059–1112","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1085–1126":"1085–1126","1040–1100":"1040–1100","–Female":"Surnud","1126":"1126","1059":"1059","1112":"1112","um 1085":"umbes 1085","1100":"1100","before 1063":"enne 1063","1085":"1085","1040":"1040","about 1100":"umbes 1100","1060":"1060","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Normandy, , , France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Sheffield, Yorkshire, England":"Sheffield, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1059–1112":"1059–1112","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1085–1126":"1085–1126","1040–1100":"1040–1100","–Female":"Kuollut","1126":"1126","1059":"1059","1112":"1112","um 1085":"noin 1085","1100":"1100","before 1063":"ennen vuotta 1063","1085":"1085","1040":"1040","about 1100":"noin 1100","1060":"1060","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Ranska","Normandy, , , France":"Normandie, Ranska","Sheffield, Yorkshire, England":"Sheffield, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1059–1112":"1059–1112","1060–Male":"1060–Décédé","1085–1126":"1085–1126","1040–1100":"1040–1100","–Female":"Décédée","1126":"1126","1059":"1059","1112":"1112","um 1085":"environ 1085","1100":"1100","before 1063":"avant 1063","1085":"1085","1040":"1040","about 1100":"environ 1100","1060":"1060","Normandie, France":"Normandie, France","Normandy, , , France":"Normandie, France","Sheffield, Yorkshire, England":"Sheffield, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Margaret de C